📍 Kwanat – Discover & Share Hidden Gems
Kwanat (from Darija, meaning "Spots" or "Good Places to Visit") is a modern, minimalist web application designed to help users share and explore great places around them. Whether it's a cozy café, a scenic lookout, or a hidden beach, Kwanat makes it easy to document, showcase, and find unique locations worth visiting.

🧠 Key Features
➕ Add a Kwan: Users can submit a new location (Kwan) by filling out a form that includes:

Title & description (with optional transportation tips)

Uploading images or videos (drag-and-drop supported)

Selecting the location on an interactive map

🗺️ Map Integration: Each Kwan is geolocated using an embedded map (OpenStreetMap via Leaflet.js) to help users visualize and navigate.

🖼️ Media Upload & Preview: Users can attach visual content (photos/videos) to better represent each spot, with live previews before submitting. File size is limited to 5MB, and supported formats are jpg, jpeg, png, and mp4.

🗂️ Responsive Grid/List View: All Kwanat are displayed in a clean, mobile-friendly layout with cards showing key information and visuals.

📱 Mobile-First UI/UX: Designed with modern, responsive, and accessible UI principles using Tailwind CSS.

🧳 Transport-Friendly: Descriptions can include instructions on how to get to the spot using local transportation (e.g., tram, taxi, walking).

🗃️ Local-First Storage: SQLite (via sql.js) handles data persistence, making the app lightweight and offline-friendly (ideal for browser-based use).

🛠️ Tech Stack
Frontend: React + Tailwind CSS

Database: SQLite (using sql.js for in-browser usage)

Map Provider: OpenStreetMap (via Leaflet.js)

Architecture: Modular component design with clean separation of logic, views, and state

🎯 Target Users
Locals who want to share their favorite hidden spots

Tourists looking for authentic, off-the-beaten-path experiences

Content creators curating city guides or local tips

Community-driven explorers and travel enthusiasts

